Citation.sTitle: Bubble Temperature Measurements on Binary Mixtures Formed by Cyclohexane at 94.7 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Bubble temperatures at 94.7 k Pa, over the entire composition range, are measured for eight binary mixtures formed by cyclohexane with 1,1,1-trichloroethane, 1,1,2,2-tetrachloroethane, epichlorohydrin, 1,2-dimethoxyethane, 1,4-dioxane, 2-picoline, N,N-dimethylformamide, and dimethylacetamide. A Swietoslawski-type ebulliometer was used for the measurements. The liquid-phase mole fraction versus temperature measurements were represented by the Wilson model.
